>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-field-group elementor-column elementor-field-type-submit elementor-col-100 e-form__buttons\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<button class=\"elementor-button elementor-size-sm\" type=\"submit\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Send<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/button>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/form>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-4badb62 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"4badb62\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-b2efa77\" data-id=\"b2efa77\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4df2636 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"4df2636\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Pavement ants and their nesting habits<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ca18186 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"ca18186\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Pavement ants are a common species of ant found all across Canada. They are small, reddish-brown ants are often seen along pavements and sidewalks. These ants are known for their ability to feed on greasy and sweet foods, making them a nuisance in homes and businesses. But what exactly are their nesting habits? Pavement ants get their name from their tendency to nest indoors and under buildings, particularly in cracks and crevices in pavement and concrete. They are a soil-nesting species, and their nests can be found in various locations, such as under rocks, in soil, and in the foundations of buildings. Pavement ants are particularly attracted to buildings with concrete slab foundations, as these provide an ideal nesting environment.<\/p><p>Their nesting habits can cause problems for homeowners and businesses alike, as pavement ant colonies can quickly grow and become a nuisance. These ants are known to forage for food over long distances and can easily find their way into homes and buildings in search of food and water. This can lead to the contamination of food and surfaces and damage to structures as the ant\u2019s tunnel through the soil and concrete.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-506c67a elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"506c67a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Diet and Behavior of Pavement Ants<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b6fdf85 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"b6fdf85\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Fire ants are small but dangerous insects that can cause severe pain and discomfort when they bite humans. The symptoms of a fire ant bite vary depending on the individual&#8217;s sensitivity to the venom and the number of bites received. Generally, a fire ant bite is characterized by an immediate burning sensation that feels like a sharp sting, followed by intense itching and swelling at the site of the bite.<\/p><p>In most cases, redness and raised bumps will also appear around the bite area, which may become painful or tender over time. Other common symptoms associated with fire ant bites include nausea, headaches, dizziness or difficulty breathing in people who are allergic to insect stings.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ac9da29 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"ac9da29\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Prevention tips for preventing fire ants from invading<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-427f12b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"427f12b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Pavement ants are a common species of ant found in many parts of Canada. These tiny insects are known for their resilience and adaptability, as they can survive in various environments. One of the fascinating aspects of pavement ants is their diet and behavior.<\/p><p>Pavement ants are omnivorous, consuming both plant and animal matter. They have been known to feed on seeds, honeydew, insects, and even small pieces of garbage. Despite their small size, pavement ants are skilled hunters and can capture and subdue prey that is much larger than themselves.<\/p><p>One of the most interesting behaviors of pavement ants is their tendency to form large colonies. These colonies can consist of thousands of ants, often found living in cracks and crevices in the pavement or other hard surfaces. The ants in these colonies work together to gather food and protect their nest from predators.<\/p><p>Regarding diet, pavement ants are particularly attracted to sweet foods. They have a unique ability to detect the presence of sugar, which is one of the primary components of their diet. Pavement ants will often form foraging trails to locate food sources and continue to follow these trails until they have exhausted the food supply.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-b274833 elementor-section-full_width elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"b274833\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;,&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-7410d75\" data-id=\"7410d75\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-8163408\" data-id=\"8163408\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e825a63 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"e825a63\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Residential Pest Control Service<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-feb1112 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"feb1112\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Customized pest control treatments can be used to safeguard your living space against bothersome pests and ensure that they don&#8217;t become a nuisance in your home.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-1f134e1 elementor-align-center elementor-widget elementor-widget-global elementor-global-4670 elementor-widget-button\" data-id=\"1f134e1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"button.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-button-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-button elementor-button-link elementor-size-lg\" href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/appointment\/\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Book An Appointment<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-0b2a4dd\" data-id=\"0b2a4dd\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-acf1e15 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"acf1e15\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-938ea46\" data-id=\"938ea46\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-52d11ed elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"52d11ed\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Pavement Ants Infestation<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6129cf4 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"6129cf4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Pavement ants are a common ant species. They get their name from their habit of nesting under pavement or concrete slabs and often enter homes through cracks in the foundation or gaps around doors and windows. Pavement ants can quickly become a nuisance when they infest homes and businesses. They forage for indoor and outdoor food, feeding on sweets, proteins, grease, and other organic matter. Once inside a structure, they can contaminate food products and damage property by excavating wood materials for nesting sites.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c1e5cc6 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"c1e5cc6\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Prevention and Control Measures<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-60a187d elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"60a187d\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Canada, like many other countries, is susceptible to pavement ant infestations. Prevention and control measures can help avoid these pesky insects from invading homes and buildings. First and foremost, preventive measures are necessary to prevent pavement ant infestations. These measures include reducing any excess moisture around the home or building, as moisture attracts pavement ants. Inspecting the home&#8217;s exterior and ensuring that the gutters and downspouts are functioning correctly can prevent excess water from accumulating near the building.<\/p><p>Additionally, sealing cracks or holes in the foundation or walls can prevent ants from entering the building. If pavement ants have already infested a building, control measures are necessary to eliminate them. DIY methods include using bait stations, insecticide sprays or dust, and vacuuming up any visible ants or ant trails. However, it is recommended to seek professional help for more severe infestations. Professional pest control methods include using residual insecticides, fumigation, and heat treatments. Identifying an infestation early on is essential to prevent it from spreading further. One can spot an infestation by the mounds of soil or sand pavement ants leave near their nests. Taking preventive measures and seeking professional help when necessary can help prevent and control pavement ant infestations in Canada.<\/p><p>If you&#8217;re experiencing an ant infestation, contact an ACME Pest Solutions representative for help. Our team of experts can help you identify the source of the insects and provide you with the best pest control services to keep your business premises free of pavement ants<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Pavement Ants Identification Color Size Description Color Pavement ants come in various colors, including brown-black or black, with slightly lighter legs and antennae. Size Pavement ants are small insects measuring around 1\/8 to 1\/16 inches. Description Pavement ants have six legs and two antennae, which they use to sense their environment. Their bodies are divided &#8230; <a title=\"Pavement Ant\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/pavement-ant\/\" aria-label=\"More on Pavement Ant\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"rank_math_lock_modified_date":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[37],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-6057","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-pest-libraries"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6057"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=6057"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6057\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=6057"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=6057"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=6057"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}